item.description:
Simple automated backup solution by using the Windows built-in tools. Create a PowerShell one-liner and add it to scheduled tasks. PowerShell one-liner:
Robocopy.exe C:\Users\ D:\Windows_backup\Backup_$(Get-Date -format &quot;dd.MM.yyyy_HH.mm.ss&quot;) /E /r:0 /w:0 /E – copy subdirectories, including empty ones;
/r – number of retries on failed copies;
/w – wait time between retries;
$(Get-Date -format &ldquo;dd.MM.yyyy_HH.mm.ss&rdquo;) – adds the current date and time to the name of the output subdirectory.
Adapt the above line to your needs and save it in a text file with a .
